<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-4877] Range queries return fewer result after a lot of delete</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4877</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi, I&apos;m testing on the trunk version&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;m using : &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;cqlsh 2.3.0 | Cassandra 1.2.0-beta1-SNAPSHOT | CQL spec 3.0.0 | Thrift protocol 19.35.0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My use case is :&lt;br/&gt;
I create a table&lt;br/&gt;
CREATE TABLE premier (&lt;br/&gt;
id int PRIMARY KEY,&lt;br/&gt;
value int&lt;br/&gt;
) WITH&lt;br/&gt;
comment=&apos;&apos; AND&lt;br/&gt;
caching=&apos;KEYS_ONLY&apos; AND&lt;br/&gt;
read_repair_chance=0.100000 AND&lt;br/&gt;
dclocal_read_repair_chance=0.000000 AND&lt;br/&gt;
gc_grace_seconds=864000 AND&lt;br/&gt;
replicate_on_write=&apos;true&apos; AND&lt;br/&gt;
compression=&lt;/p&gt;
{&apos;sstable_compression&apos;: &apos;SnappyCompressor&apos;}
&lt;p&gt;;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) I insert 10 000 000 rows (they are like id = 1 and value =1)&lt;br/&gt;
2) I delete 2 000 000 rows (i use random method to choose the key value)&lt;br/&gt;
3) I do select * from premier ; and my result is 7944 instead of 10 000.&lt;br/&gt;
4) if if do select * from premier limit 20000 ; my result is 15839 .&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So after a lot of delete, the range operator is not working.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
